            "description": "<html><body><article data-scroll-anchor=\"true\" data-testid=\"conversation-turn-38\" data-turn=\"assistant\" data-turn-id=\"request-WEB:e9106a77-4a7d-4920-b3c3-e079f1bf0b9f-18\" dir=\"auto\" tabindex=\"-1\"><div tabindex=\"-1\"><div data-message-author-role=\"assistant\" data-message-id=\"88863ace-13c9-45c0-a585-1c7b4147284a\" data-message-model-slug=\"gpt-5-mini\" dir=\"auto\">\n<ul>\n<li data-end=\"230\" data-start=\"80\">\n<span>Radian Group (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/RDN\" title=\"Radian Group Inc.\">RDN</a></span>) on Thursday said that, e</span>ffective February 12, Sumita Pandit has resigned as CFO and president of the company.</li>\n<li data-end=\"230\" data-start=\"80\">The board appointed Daniel Kobell, 46, and Robert J. Quigley, 54, to elevated senior executive vice president roles in the company’s finance function.</li>\n<li>Kobell was appointed senior executive vice president, interim CFO, reporting to Richard Thornberry, the company’s CEO.</li>\n<li>Source: <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/filing/155662255\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Filing \">Filing </a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-eci=\"true\"> </p>\n</div></div></article><div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
